 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.82","title":"[audit][stream] Add cooperative poll budgets to Count/Collect/Fold terminal futures","description":"Count, Collect, and Fold currently loop inside a single poll call until the upstream stream yields Pending or None. With an always-ready stream, one poll can monopolize the executor indefinitely. Add a bounded per-poll budget with wake_by_ref handoff so these terminal futures remain cooperative, preserve accumulation semantics across polls, and add focused regressions for always-ready streams that exceed the budget.","notes":"Implemented cooperative poll budgets in src/stream/count.rs, src/stream/collect.rs, and src/stream/fold.rs so terminal futures yield after bounded always-ready drains instead of monopolizing one poll call. Added focused regressions: count_yields_after_budget_on_always_ready_stream, collect_yields_after_budget_on_always_ready_stream, and fold_yields_after_budget_on_always_ready_stream. Validation: local rustfmt on touched files passed; `rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-jadetower-1qfd0-82-check cargo check -p asupersync --lib` passed; `rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-jadetower-1qfd0-82-test2 cargo test -p asupersync yields_after_budget_on_always_ready_stream -- --nocapture` passed (including the three new regressions). `ubs --only=rust` on touched files only reported generic test-only panic markers. Remaining blocker: remote `cargo clippy -p asupersync --lib -- -D warnings` failed on worker vmi1227854 with `/tmp` exhaustion (`No space left on device`), not with a code diagnostic.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"JadeTower","created_at":"2026-03-10T05:37:44.590658458Z","created_by":"JadeTower","updated_at":"2026-03-10T06:00:57.181206646Z","closed_at":"2026-03-10T06:00:57.181178865Z","close_reason":"Implemented cooperative poll budgets in src/stream/count.rs, src/stream/collect.rs, and src/stream/fold.rs; added focused always-ready regressions for each; validated with remote `cargo check -p asupersync --lib` and remote targeted `cargo test -p asupersync yields_after_budget_on_always_ready_stream -- --nocapture` passing. Remaining failed lanes are unrelated/global: `cargo clippy -p asupersync --lib -- -D warnings` fails on pre-existing `src/runtime/state.rs` too-many-lines lint, and `cargo check --all-targets` remote run timed out before completion; local fail-open was cancelled to honor offload-only constraints.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","stream"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.82","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-10T05:37:44.590658458Z","created_by":"JadeTower"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.83","title":"[audit][stream] Make Any/All yield cooperatively on long always-ready runs","description":"src/stream/any_all.rs loops in Any::poll and All::poll until match/end/pending. On always-ready streams with no early-exit (Any predicate always false, All predicate always true), a single poll can monopolize the executor indefinitely. Add a bounded per-poll scan budget with wake_by_ref handoff, preserve early-exit semantics, add focused regression tests for always-ready long runs, and validate via rch-backed cargo commands.","notes":"Implemented cooperative fairness guard in src/stream/any_all.rs: added ANY_ALL_COOPERATIVE_BUDGET (1024), bounded scan loops in Any::poll and All::poll, and wake_by_ref handoff on budget exhaustion. Added focused regressions any_yields_after_budget_when_predicate_never_matches and all_yields_after_budget_when_predicate_stays_true using always-ready synthetic streams and tracked self-wake assertions. Validation: rustfmt --edition 2024 src/stream/any_all.rs passed; rch exec -- cargo check -p asupersync --lib passed; rch exec -- cargo test -p asupersync any_yields_after_budget_when_predicate_never_matches -- --nocapture passed (targeted test green). Repo gates via rch: cargo check --all-targets passed; cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings is blocked by unrelated existing lint at src/runtime/state.rs:2259 (clippy::too_many_lines); cargo fmt --check is blocked by unrelated pre-existing formatting drift in benches/tracing_overhead.rs and src/net/tcp/listener.rs.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"EmeraldPeak","created_at":"2026-03-10T05:39:57.083747372Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-10T06:09:16.760656147Z","closed_at":"2026-03-10T06:09:16.760613247Z","close_reason":"Completed cooperative Any/All fairness fix with targeted rch validation; remaining clippy/fmt failures are unrelated repo frontiers","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","stream"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.83","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-10T05:39:57.083747372Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.84","title":"[audit][stream] Make ForEach/ForEachAsync yield cooperatively on always-ready runs","description":"src/stream/for_each.rs currently loops in Future::poll for both ForEach and ForEachAsync until upstream Pending/None. On always-ready streams (especially with immediate async closures), one poll can process unbounded items and monopolize the executor. Add bounded per-poll budgets with wake_by_ref handoff while preserving completion and side-effect ordering semantics; add focused always-ready regression tests and validate with rch-backed cargo commands.","notes":"Implemented cooperative fairness guard in src/stream/for_each.rs: added FOR_EACH_COOPERATIVE_BUDGET (1024), bounded per-poll work in ForEach::poll and ForEachAsync::poll, and wake_by_ref handoff when budget is exhausted. Added focused regressions for always-ready behavior: for_each_yields_after_budget_on_always_ready_stream and for_each_async_yields_after_budget_on_immediate_futures, asserting bounded progress, self-wake signaling, and completion on re-poll. Validation: rustfmt --edition 2024 src/stream/for_each.rs passed; rch exec -- cargo check -p asupersync --lib passed; rch exec -- cargo test -p asupersync for_each_yields_after_budget_on_always_ready_stream -- --nocapture passed; rch exec -- cargo test -p asupersync for_each_async_yields_after_budget_on_immediate_futures -- --nocapture passed; rch exec -- cargo check --all-targets passed. Repo-wide clippy/fmt remain blocked by unrelated existing frontiers: src/runtime/state.rs:2259 (clippy::too_many_lines) and formatting drift in benches/tracing_overhead.rs + src/net/tcp/listener.rs.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"EmeraldPeak","created_at":"2026-03-10T06:09:58.461032288Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-10T06:19:17.592516085Z","closed_at":"2026-03-10T06:19:17.592496960Z","close_reason":"Completed cooperative ForEach/ForEachAsync fairness fix with targeted rch validation; remaining clippy/fmt failures are unrelated repo frontiers","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","stream"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.84","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-10T06:09:58.461032288Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.85","title":"[audit][stream] Make Debounce yield cooperatively on always-ready bursts","description":"src/stream/debounce.rs still drains immediately-ready upstream items in an unbounded loop before it evaluates the buffered quiet period. If the inner stream keeps returning Ready(Some(_)) synchronously, Debounce can monopolize a single executor poll forever, repeatedly replacing the pending item and never yielding. Add a bounded per-poll burst drain budget with self-wake handoff so debounce remains cooperative without changing quiet-period semantics, add focused regression coverage for an always-ready stream, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"SunnyMountain","created_at":"2026-03-10T16:36:27.682392704Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-10T16:36:27.682392704Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.85","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-10T16:36:27.682392704Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
